        "topFinding": "The stalled god-file decomposition finally moved hard (gameplay.gd 2878 to 1354, hud 2036 to 905, iso_grid 2160 to 1295, unit 1845 to 1138, eleven clean RefCounted modules), closing the chronic \"target gameplay.gd next\" action. But most of it (wave 2: 6 modified + 11 new modules, 332 insertions / 1696 deletions) sits UNCOMMITTED against commit_per_patch_on_br, gated only by a line-count ratchet and a static smoke test that never execute the moved runtime logic, so a behavior-identical refactor of the exact collision/pathfinding surface that already cost five patch cycles could ship a regression undetected. That risk dropped reliability 74 to 48 and performance 83 to 68 and pulled health 82 to 78, though nothing is broken: the game builds, ships, saves, and plays the M1 loop and both hard-rule gates pass. Near-term: commit wave 2 as one patch and regen the ratchet baseline, stand up the long-absent pathfinding/collision test harness before trusting the extraction, and clear the four chronic anchors now six runs open.",
